### Description

Currently, detecting whether the code runs on the server or browser requires using:

```ts
import { isPlatformBrowser, isPlatformServer } from '@angular/common';
import { inject, PLATFORM_ID } from '@angular/core';

const platformId = inject(PLATFORM_ID);
if (isPlatformBrowser(platformId)) { ... }
```

While this works, it introduces unnecessary boilerplate and dependency injection even in simple cases.

### Proposed solution

Introduce simple built-in helpers that rely on the global `ngServerMode` flag to detect the execution environment:

```ts
export function isServer() {
  return typeof ngServerMode !== 'undefined' && ngServerMode;
}

export function isBrowser() {
  return !isServer();
}
```
This approach is similar to how Angular already uses `ngServerMode` internally to determine server rendering.

