### Description

With `21.0.0-next.10` vitest produces several false reports for the covered branches.

### Minimal Reproduction

This can already be observed when creating a new project, installing `@vitest/coverage-v8` and running `ng test --no-watch --coverage`:

<img width="547" height="91" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/418c8643-84ce-4440-af83-d57000cb6bb0" />

Here is a larger example that showcases several instances:

```typescript
protected readonly title = signal('next-ten');

protected readonly someInput = input.required<string>();

constructor() {
  if (true) {
    console.log(this.title());
  }
}
```

<img width="518" height="174" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/106b5c04-9b94-42fc-b9b0-2b22d7139dd7" />

I also observed (so far only in a pipe) that implemented interfaces are not reported as covered:

```typescript
@Pipe({
  name: 'myTransform',
})
export class MyTransformPipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(value: string, ...args: unknown[]): unknown {
    return value.toUpperCase();
  }
}
```
```typescript
describe('MyTransformPipe', () => {
  it('create an instance', () => {
    const pipe = new MyTransformPipe();
    expect(pipe).toBeTruthy();
    expect(pipe.transform('test')).toBe('TEST');
  });
});
```

<img width="515" height="99" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2bad9f6b-e080-4723-a7d7-b0a7cfbc0fb7" />


Some more context:

Setting `aot` to `false` results in almost all lines getting covered. Only the `if (true)` case still reports that the else path was not taken.
With `aot=false`, karma produces 100% coverage.
But with `aot=true`, karma only reports these findings:

